{
  "stem": "11472.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And he really came-- he knew my father was a businessman.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "He knew he had money, to my grandparents.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And he said, I have permission from the Gestapo from Borschtov to-- to take a few men, and give them badges.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They would have a badge.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And with this badge, they would have a permit-- if they have enough money to pay off the Gestapo.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And then you have to pay the Gestapo like every month-- and they have enough money to buy a horse and wagon back from the peasants, they can go in the villages and collect scrap iron and old materials for the German government.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Three people from our family bought those badges.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "My father, Fischel Dodek bought that badge, my grandfather Zayde Stermer bought that badge, and my uncle Nisel Stermer.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And my God, this was a miracle.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "They could leave our town, and they could bring us back a bread, a piece of bread, a chicken-- I don't think we never had a chicken.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "You know, but bread-- they could bring back a little bit of flour, some potatoes, you know.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And they were free to travel around in the villages.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And that's when they started-- the peasants and some people were telling them that they're having aktions in other towns.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "We wanted to know what is an aktia?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What is an action?",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They say they come in, they surround the town, the ghetto, and they come in, and they take everybody out.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "People started to scramble to look for-- to make bunkers, to hide.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In my grandmother Esther's house there were six bunkers.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Not one bunker was ever discovered.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Underground.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And under the ground, yeah.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "What can I tell you?",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
